This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user is an algorithm developer on a hackathon project building an on-demand desk booking system. They requested:
   1. Read PLAN.md and suggest algorithmic approaches for AssignmentService
   2. Implement Simulated Annealing with 12 threads, 48 runs (later bumped to 400 by user), pick best result
   3. Write a test using real data files with 191 random employees
   4. Refine test to only use Martin Dow's subordinates (depth-4 and below), exclude non-real desks (Flexible Working/Pods), set all SocialPreference to NONE
   5. Remove per-team output grouping; show flat list sorted by desk name for vibing proximity
   6. (Abandoned) Lower window preference weight — user said "don't worry about the window for now"
   7. **Current pending task:** Commit and push all changes, output SA test results into frontend stubs.ts, start the frontend for visualization

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Quadratic Assignment Problem (QAP): minimize ∑ weight(i,j) × distance(desk(i), desk(j))
   - Simulated Annealing: random start, swap moves, temperature cooling, accept bad moves with probability exp(-delta/T)
   - Incremental delta O(n) per swap: only terms involving swapped persons change
   - LCA (Lowest Common Ancestor) via orgPath prefix matching for tree distance
   - Weight formula: teamWeight (1/treeDistance) + socialTerm + luckyAffinity
   - Multi-threading: ExecutorService(12 threads), 48→400 independent SA runs, best cost wins
   - Java: Jersey/JAX-RS, Guice DI, JUnit 5, Jackson JSON
   - React/TypeScript frontend with stub API layer (stubs.ts)
   - Floor map: 191 desks, coordinates 0–6736 × 0–4290, neighborhood grouping
   - Org chart: 3895 employees, tree structure with depth and orgPath (root-to-self list)
   - Martin Dow: id="75_Martin_Dow", depth=3, 343 subordinates, 5 direct reports at depth 4

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`src/main/java/com/starlingbank/service/SimulatedAnnealingAssignmentService.java`** (CREATED)
     - Core SA implementation. Key constants (after user changed NUM_RUNS to 400):
     ```java
     private static final int NUM_RUNS = 400;
     private static final int NUM_THREADS = 12;
     private static final int ITERATIONS = 200_000;
     private static final double INITIAL_TEMPERATURE = 10_000.0;
     private static final double COOLING_RATE = 0.9999;
     ```
     - Weight formula:
     ```java
     double weight = teamWeight(bi.getEmployeeId(), bj.getEmployeeId(), orgNodes)
             + socialTerm(bi.getSocialPreference(), bj.getSocialPreference())
             + luckyAffinity(bi, bj, luckyTargetId);
     ```
     - Social term (per user correction — both introverts attract):
     ```java
     private double socialTerm(SocialPreference si, SocialPreference sj) {
         boolean iQuiet = si == SocialPreference.DONT_TALK_TO_ME;
         boolean jQuiet = sj == SocialPreference.DONT_TALK_TO_ME;
         boolean iTalk  = si == SocialPreference.TALK_TO_ME;
         boolean jTalk  = sj == SocialPreference.TALK_TO_ME;
         if (iTalk && jTalk) return 2.0;
         if (iQuiet && jQuiet) return 2.0;
         if (iQuiet != jQuiet) return -3.0;
         return 0.0;
     }
     ```
     - LCA tree distance:
     ```java
     private int treeDistance(OrgNode a, OrgNode b) {
         List<String> pathA = a.getOrgPath();
         List<String> pathB = b.getOrgPath();
         int minLen = Math.min(pathA.size(), pathB.size());
         int lcaDepth = -1;
         for (int i = 0; i < minLen; i++) {
             if (pathA.get(i).equals(pathB.get(i))) lcaDepth = i;
             else break;
         }
         if (lcaDepth < 0) return Integer.MAX_VALUE / 2;
         return (pathA.size() - 1 - lcaDepth) + (pathB.size() - 1 - lcaDepth);
     }
     ```
     - Incremental delta (O(n) per swap):
     ```java
     private double computeSwapDelta(int p, int q, int[] deskForPerson,
                                     double[][] weight, double[][] dist, int n) {
         int dp = deskForPerson[p];
         int dq = deskForPerson[q];
         double delta = 0.0;
         for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
             if (k == p || k == q) continue;
             int dk = deskForPerson[k];
             delta += weight[p][k] * (dist[dq][dk] - dist[dp][dk]);
             delta += weight[q][k] * (dist[dp][dk] - dist[dq][dk]);
         }
         return delta;
     }
     ```
     - Multi-thread dispatch:
     ```java
     ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(NUM_THREADS);
     List<Future<RunResult>> futures = new ArrayList<>(NUM_RUNS);
     for (int r = 0; r < NUM_RUNS; r++) {
         final int runId = r;
         futures.add(executor.submit(() -> runSA(runId, n, m, weightMatrix, distMatrix)));
     }
     ```

   - **`src/main/java/com/starlingbank/AppModule.java`** (MODIFIED by both dev and user/linter)
     ```java
     bind(HelloService.class).to(HelloServiceImpl.class);
     bind(FloorMapService.class).to(FloorMapServiceImpl.class);
     bind(AssignmentService.class).to(SimulatedAnnealingAssignmentService.class);
     ```
     Note: User/linter added the FloorMapService binding.

   - **`src/test/java/com/starlingbank/service/SimulatedAnnealingAssignmentServiceTest.java`** (CREATED)
     - Key constant: `private static final String MARTIN_DOW_ID = "75_Martin_Dow";`
     - @BeforeAll loads both JSON files. Critical null-fix for neighborhood:
     ```java
     JsonNode nbNode = d.get("neighborhood");
     String neighborhood = (nbNode == null || nbNode.isNull()) ? null : nbNode.asText();
     desks.add(new Desk(d.get("id").asText(), d.get("name").asText(), neighborhood,
             d.get("x").asDouble(), d.get("y").asDouble(), d.get("rotation").asDouble()));
     ```
     - OrgNode parsing (JSON field names differ from Java model):
     ```java
     String parentId = n.get("parent").isNull() ? null : n.get("parent").asText();
     List<String> childrenIds = new ArrayList<>();
     n.get("children").forEach(c -> childrenIds.add(c.asText()));
     List<String> orgPath = new ArrayList<>();
     n.get("orgPath").forEach(p -> orgPath.add(p.asText()));
     orgNodes.put(id, new OrgNode(id, parentId, childrenIds, n.get("depth").asInt(), orgPath));
     ```
     - Real desk filter (170 desks):
     ```java
     List<Desk> realDesks = desks.stream()
             .filter(d -> d.getNeighborhood() != null && !d.getNeighborhood().equals("Desk Pods"))
             .toList();
     ```
     - BFS from Martin's children, pick 170:
     ```java
     Deque<String> queue = new ArrayDeque<>(orgNodes.get(MARTIN_DOW_ID).getChildrenIds());
     while (!queue.isEmpty()) {
         String id = queue.poll();
         subtree.add(id);
         queue.addAll(orgNodes.get(id).getChildrenIds());
